  "prompt": "Does Congress party digging their grave slowly as they are opposing everything done by PM Modi like saying Jay Shriram or surgical strikes?",
  "response": "The Congress Party's position in Indian politics is complex and influenced by various factors, including their response to the policies and actions of the ruling party, BJP, led by PM Modi. Critics of the Congress Party argue that focusing on opposing everything related to the BJP may alienate certain voter segments and fail to offer a compelling alternative vision. \n\nHowever, the success or failure of a political party often depends on several factors, including its ability to connect with the electorate, present a clear ideological stance, and effectively communicate its policies. The issues of nationalism, defense policy, and cultural sentiments, such as the significance of phrases like \"Jay Shriram,\" can resonate deeply with voters, and a party's stance on these matters can influence its electoral success.\n\nUltimately, the impact of the Congress Party's strategy will depend on how well they can position themselves in the evolving political landscape and address the concerns of their constituents while also shaping public opinion in their favor.",
